## For regression:
# Leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) (low bias hign variance)
data = as.data.frame(cbind(x=c(1:100),y=c(405:504))  ) #a fake data

glm.fit = glm(y ~ x , data=data)
library(boot)
cv.err = cv.glm(data,glm.fit)
cv.err$delta
#k-Fold Cross-Validation
cv.err = cv.glm(data,glm.fit,K=10)

Bootstrapping

Bootstrapping uses resampling from the data with replacement to approximate the sampling distribution of an estimate.

1000sizesize

boot(data="your data here", statistic=fun, R=1000)

library(boot)
##bootstrap (sampling w replacement)
boot.fn = function(data,index){
  return( coef( lm(y ~ x ,data=data,subset=index) ) )
}

data=as.data.frame(cbind(x=c(1,2,3,4,5),y=c(4,5,7,8,9))  ) #a fake data

boot.fn(data ,1:5) #to all data unit
boot.fn(data,sample(5,5,replace=T))
b = boot(data ,boot.fn ,1000) #resampling 1000 times 
# bias=mean(b$t) - b$t0 (est. - original)
summary(b)
